        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 31 at 5:22PM EDT by NWS Greenville-Spartanburg SC</headline>
        <description>At 522 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 4
miles southwest of Sylva, or near Webster, moving southeast at 10
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.

Locations impacted include...
Sylva, Cullowhee, Webster, Dillsboro, and Savannah.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
